{"article_id":"LNuUdvbXPAIWNq2Q","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"In the main , politics is not a dispute over facts , but over values .","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"Twitter risks blurring the distinction .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"No American ,","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"not even the president , has an inherent right to a social-media account .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Tech companies such as Facebook and Twitter are free to ban any user","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"they see fit .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"They ' re free to fact-check anyone","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"they want ,","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"to create a framework of acceptable speech ,","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"and to enforce their policies either consistently or capriciously .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"They ' re free to accuse Donald Trump","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"- and only Trump ,","depth":11},{"id":12,"text":"if they see fit -","depth":11},{"id":13,"text":"of being a liar .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"They ' re free to do all of these things .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Yesterday ,","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"after years of pressure from media and Democrats ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"Twitter labeled two of Trump ' s tweets","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"- in which he had claimed","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"that the use of mail-in ballots for large numbers of people would be \" substantially fraudulent \"","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"and result in a \" rigged election \" -","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"as \" potentially misleading. \"","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"It ' s a mistake for any platform to drop its neutral stance","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"and take on fact-checking duties , a task","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"that ' s going to be impossible to accomplish either objectively or effectively .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"It ' s going to corrode trust in the brand ,","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"but it won ' t change a single mind .","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"Once Twitter begins tagging some tweets and not others with \" what you need to know , \"","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"it will be staking out partisan positions .","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"The Trump tweets","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"that precipitated its first election-related fact-check","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"are a good example of this .","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"It would have been far more reasonable for the social-media giant to label Trump ' s ugly and libelous tweets about Joe Scarborough as misleading .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"Instead , Twitter decided to inaugurate its policy","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"by alleging","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"that Trump had dishonestly claimed","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"that mail-in ballots would lead to \" a Rigged Election . \"","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"Even if this contention were entirely baseless ,","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"it would be as untrue","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"as saying Russia rigged the election","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"- a claim","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"that politicians such as Adam Schiff and Nancy Pelosi , along with most major media outlets , have been making for years .","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"while the president ' s rhetoric about voting is debatable ,","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"it is also well within the normal parameters of contemporary political discourse .","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"It ' s not exactly \" unsubstantiated \" to assert","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that more mail-in ballots \" would lead to voter fraud , \"","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"as Twitter holds .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"There are dozens of instances of potential voter fraud","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"investigated every year .","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"The Heritage Foundation has cataloged 1,285 prosecuted cases .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"Which is to say","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that contending that \" voter fraud \" is a problem is no more misleading","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"than contending","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"tax cuts will hurt the poor","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"or that repealing net-neutrality rules will destroy the Internet .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"In practice , \" voter fraud \" is no more a conspiracy theory","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"than is \" voter suppression. \"","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"Both happen on occasion ,","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"yet there is no evidence","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"that either has toppled the outcome of any modern election .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"The problem is that only one of these two issues will earn a \" more information \" tag from Twitter ,","depth":4},{"id":62,"text":"because only one of these two issues offends the sensibilities of the liberals","depth":5},{"id":63,"text":"whose concerns Twitter ultimately cares about .","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"In another tweet , Trump claims","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"that everyone in California will be mailed a ballot .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"This is factually untrue .","depth":5},{"id":67,"text":"But so is the pinned tweet of the Democratic Party ' s presumptive nominee , Joe Biden :","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"\" I can ' t believe","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"I have to say this ,","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"but please don ' t drink bleach. \"","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"The president never instructed anyone to drink bleach ,","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"yet Biden repeats this incessantly , along with numerous other misleading statements about his record and GOP policies .","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"Which brings us to the problem :","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"Whom will Twitter designate as its judge ?","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"Its fact-checking page redirects users to debunkings of the president ' s tweets by partisan operatives such as Vox ' s Aaron Rupar and CNN ' s Daniel Dale","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"- two figures","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"who possess no expertise","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"gauging policy outcomes","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"and who are quite often dishonest","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"and misleading themselves .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"As for CNN , the Washington Post , Vox , HuffPost , and the other outlets","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"featured on the page -","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"they deceive their audiences with far more sophistication than the president .","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"These outlets like to appeal to the authority of experts ,","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"but not experts","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"whose conclusions contradict their own .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"There is a reason","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"we debate issues","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"rather than appoint Truth Magistrates","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"to hand down verdicts :","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"For the most part , politics is a dispute not over facts but over values .","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"As is often the case ,","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"Trump immediately ceded the high ground","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"by threatening to \" strongly regulate \" or shut down social-media platforms .","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"Such threats are nothing new for this president ,","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"who has often menaced media with regulations and legal action ,","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"although one can not help but notice a paradox .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"Trump rarely follows through on his destructive threats","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to inhibit speech","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"but does follow through on his promise","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"to cram the courts full of judges","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"who have deference for First Amendment ,","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"while those","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"who talk in the most lofty terms about the press","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"tend to pressure tech companies to constrain interactions , to ban accounts , and to \" fact-check \" their partisan foes .","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"The distress over social media is predicated on the idea","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"that average Americans are too dim","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"to grapple with the messiness of unfettered speech .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"Many leftists","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"- those","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"who wanted to institute Fairness Doctrines","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"or overturn Citizens United -","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"admit this openly","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"when they suggest","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"that unregulated speech is corroding \" democracy . \"","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"Trump is the first president","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"to truly take advantage of direct , instantaneous access to millions of Americans .","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"Whether this is helpful to his cause is debatable .","depth":6},{"id":119,"text":"Certainly , we are blessed","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"that the president ' s policies and rhetoric are often disconnected .","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"Whatever the case , though , we have an entire industry","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"that stands ready to challenge the veracity if his statements .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"We don ' t need Twitter to join in the fact-checking game .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"Silicon Valley doesn ' t have the resources , knowledge , or people","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"to do it correctly .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":251,"left":186,"right":250,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":127,"right":185,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":185,"left":139,"right":184,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":139,"left":128,"right":138,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":2,"ri